Ask HN: Google for Summarized Results
text:
Nowadays, many posts/articles are long (for SEO). More often then not, my searches are about every specific thing, and the answer could easily be a paragraph.

So I started Laste, the goal to be a search engine, but the results are summarised (a paragraph or 2)

Would you be interested in using some like that? What's your thoughts?

In case interested, you can subscribe here https://laste.co

Thanks!

Ask HN: What do you use to monitor hardware in the field?
text: We are a B2B that has hardware running Linux in the field for a bunch of customers at their site (let's round to like 1000 machines and growing). All of them "connect" to our servers through OpenVPN and have been, from "days gone past", loaded with Zabbix and send us telemetry. Unfortunately due to personnel changes, no one is really sure of how things are done anymore and the task of maintaining this monitoring is coming down to me. How would you approach this task? I'm feeling a bit overwhelmed and reading online kinda want to just start over by choosing something newer like Prometheus.

For sale: 8 hours/week of my time
text:
I have a full time job as a software engineer that I enjoy. I work 4 10-hour days and have Fridays off. High inflation and increased expenses are driving me back into the job market looking for ways to supplement my income, but I don't want to fight for gigs on freelance platforms like Upwork.

Ideally I want a reliable project where I can invest 8-12 hours per week. One idea I had was to offer my services to companies looking to fill full time roles as a 'bridge' employee until they find their full time candidate (I could even participate in the interview process).

I guess I'm looking for a 'long term gig'. Am I nuts? Or is there a job board out there for companies/startups that need just a bit of extra help?

Show HN: LokiList – Decentralized Casual Encounters
text:
FOSTA killed Craigslist Casual Encounters by attacking the Section 230 safe harbor protection.

Therefore, I made a Casual Encounters that doesn't need any Section 230 safe harbor protection.

All user interaction occurs via Session Private Messenger, a decentralized end-to-end encrypted messaging network.

No cookies, javascript, or registration required.
